function Ucuda({Awl:a,Xxl:b}){const c=[];b&&c.push('The PRE-IDENTIFIED STEPS below have already been distilled from the screenshots by a separate model in earlier batches. Treat them as the primary structural guide for the workflow — each step represents a "key moment" of the workflow. Where present, a time range in parentheses (e.g. "(12.30–17.50s)") gives the window of the recording the step covers; use it to align steps with the screenshots and audio, but do not surface raw timestamps in the diagram. The attached screenshots are supporting context — consult them when a step is ambiguous, and avoid introducing new steps that contradict this list unless there is sufficient evidence in the screenshots or audio transcript that clearly calls for it. If an audio narration transcript is also provided, use it primarily to refine step intent and labeling; an explicit, clear narration is also valid evidence for the exception above.');c.push('Screenshots are sequential frames from a screen recording, ordered by filename. Ignore frames that only show cursor movement or loading states. Also ignore frames that only show the Lucid app or its AI chat panel — those are recording artifacts — unless the captured workflow is itself about using Lucid. If you can\'t tell what changed between two frames, skip them rather than guessing. If the same screen or interaction appears repeatedly with only the entity (row, team, item, account) changing, represent it as a labeled iteration loop with a decision node ("More X to process?"), not as enumerated repetitions.');
a&&c.push('Audio narration: a transcript of the user narrating while performing the workflow. Use it to understand intent and to label steps. If narration describes repeating the same work across multiple instances (teams, teammates, rows, items), represent that as a labeled iteration loop with a decision node (e.g. "More teams to update?"), not as separate enumerated steps. If narration and screenshots disagree, trust the screenshots for what happened and the narration for why.');c.push('Collapse consecutive "review", "inspect", or "look at" actions on the same view into a single step.');
